Spec: SpecDD Explain Skill

Purpose:
  Guide agents in explaining a SpecDD spec or effective spec chain in human language.

Owns:
  ./specdd-explain/SKILL.md.ejs
  ./specdd-explain/agents/openai.yaml

Must:
  Identify the requested spec, target path, feature, behavior, or changed file.
  Read the active bootstrap chain before the applicable spec or effective spec chain.
  Read explicit `References` only when they materially affect the explanation.
  Explain requested specs succinctly, clearly, and with enough depth to understand the feature or area under contract.
  Explain what the contract means in plain language rather than line by line.
  Cover relevant purpose, scope, ownership, allowed changes, behavior, boundaries, dependencies, scenarios, examples, tasks, and completion criteria.
  Preserve the active spec scope, constraints, boundaries, and observable behavior.
  Distinguish direct spec content from inference, missing context, and underspecified behavior.
  Keep framework mechanics brief unless the user asks how SpecDD resolution works.

Must not:
  Edit files while explaining unless explicitly requested.
  Add behavior, guarantees, workflows, or authority unsupported by the active specs.
  Treat explanation as changing the spec contract.
  Expand into sibling specs unless the active spec references them or they are needed to avoid a misleading explanation.

Depends on:
  ../fragments/bootstrap-resolution.md.ejs
  ../fragments/spec-chain-resolution.md.ejs
